node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY on September 10, 2021 tagging @michzsimmons, and @redhot_challenges. May be an image of one or more people, balloon and text.

node.text:
Happy Friday and Challenge Announcement Day, JJMP fam!! 🥳🎉🙋🏻‍♀️
I am delighted to announce Michelle @michzsimmons as our JJMP Guest Mod for this weekend’s challenge!! I enjoyed learning she is from Atlanta, GA which is not far from where I live, and I think you will also enjoy hearing the backstory of her and her stunning shot! 🤩🌟 
.
Please give her a warm JJMP welcome and then get to tagging your own de-lightful images!! 🤗💛 ☑️ 
.
.
.
.
“Hi fellow mobile photographers! My name is Michelle (@michzsimmons), and I’m so honored to be the guest mod for this weekend’s challenge. Thanks to Dee (@iheart_alfresco_photos) and Jax (@jaxkm2) for inviting me to take part in this challenge. I’ll do my best to choose the images thoughtfully and earnestly.

I began my photographic journey about 3-1/2 years ago. I started college on an art scholarship but switched majors after 3 years. After a long career in electrical engineering, discovering photography gave me the artistic outlet I’d been longing for all these years. Mobile photography is now my true love!

The photo above was actually created by mistake, which happens a lot and often produces my best work. I had attempted a photo with car headlights in the background several times with no luck. This fourth attempt was no different, and my daughter was tired of modeling! As I packed up, I found a photography smoke bomb in my trunk and as a last resort, I set the smoke bomb off in front of the headlights. It wasn’t the shot I originally wanted, but I loved the resulting silhouette and backlighting.

So show me your best backlighting images! If you created the backlighting on purpose, tell me about that in your post, too. I’ll be looking for creativity, impact and originality, so good luck to you all 😁.” ~ Michelle @michzsimmons 
.
.
Theme: Backlighting 
.
.
‼️Challenge Rules:‼️
▶️ MUST be following @jj_mobilephotography
▶️ Specify which mobile device you’re using.
.
.
Tag #jj_mobilephoto_324 👈
.
.
▶️New or old photos okay
.
▶️No previously featured (here on @jj_mobilephotography) photos please
.
#jj_mp_michzsimmons 
Please pay our featured artist’s gallery a visit and show it some jjmp L❤️VE. Thanks!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY in Saguaro National Park-Tucson Mountain District with @allophile_. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Hello everyone! It’s Dee again to share my final feature of the night with you!😊 🙋🏻‍♀️
.
.
There’s nothing dry and dusty about this desert sunset shot by Joe @allophile_ , is there?? 😍 🏜
The Saguaro cactus silhouettes make a striking centerpiece against the amazing array of colors of what Joe identified as “the monsoon skies”. 
Of course, I had to look that up, 🤓 and below is what I found: 

“For a few months each year, the Desert Southwest transforms into a storm photographer’s paradise. Nourishing rains pour from the sky in daily deluges. Hulking thunderheads tap the desert heat to soar higher than jetliners fly. Bolts of electricity light up the sky as bursts of wind descend to the ground, kicking up vast clouds of dust…..
Strictly speaking, a monsoon is a seasonal wind shift, but when it arrives, it’s like flipping a switch. The ordinarily arid desert landscape quickly becomes a minefield of thunderstorms….” ⛈ 🏜 
.
.
“Like flipping a switch….” I love that description 🤩 and can certainly see why this time of year “lights” Joe’s photography energy  up in a BIG way!! 💫 📱 
.
Please take a moment to visit Joe’s “electric” gallery @allophile_ and share lots of warm JJMP love  while you’re there!!!! 😊🧡💙
.
.
I look forward to seeing you next week!😃🙋🏻‍♀️ Dee (@iheart_alfresco_photos) 
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY in Hudson River Waterfront Walkway with @apeaseye. May be an image of body of water.

node.text:
“Attention, JJMP shoppers”🙋🏻‍♀️ 
It’s Dee here and I hope you are having an extra special day today!! 🤗 🤍🙏🏼 
.
.
💙💡 This Blue light special that Allison @apeaseye captured and tagged to our DOF weeklong challenge (@jj_mobilephoto_dof ) caught my eye and helped get me out of the early morning fog I was still in while scrolling. 🌫 👌 (Maybe I also need more of that delicious coffee or tea from our last 2 dof challenge features. 😅☕️👍)
.
.
This appealing shot has many features going for it, besides the successful shallow-to-medium DOF that Allison achieved. 
I love the leading line of the curved railing, and the BNW-but-not look that this foggy morning  on the Hudson River creates. 
.
This wet, watery shot is also a good opportunity to remember our fellow JJMP friends and family in NYC and surrounding areas that suffered such devastating flooding and loss last week due to tropical storm Ida.😢❤️😙
*
*
💡And on a lighter note, I would also REALLY love to see a show of 🤚’s below, for any of you, especially those outside of the USA, that know or still use the term “blue light special.” I’m very curious if it transcended beyond 🇺🇸 or ⏰. 🤓😘💙
.
.
After that, Please take some time to visit Allison’s wonderful gallery @apeaseye and spread lots of JJMP love and light while you’re there too!💙🤍

I’ll be back to share one more  feature with you this evening!! 😃🙋🏻‍♀️ Dee @iheart_alfresco_photos
.
.
